==Spanish==

===Noun===
'''porteño'''
# Inhabitant of Buenos Aires (which is nowadays officially called ''Buenos Aires Autonomous City'').  '''[[Bonaerense]]''' is not synonymous with '''Porteño'''.

A porteño usually has as a natural part of his language the Lunfardo slang. First created by Italian, Spanish, and Irish immigrants who were also very related with the Tango culture, the Lunfardo and its incorporation into the language amongst the citizens of Buenos Aires is still as alive as it was in its begginings, with the cultural differences and advancements time has given to its own particular ever-growing dictionary of made-up words.

